Embattled Nairobi County Clerk Edward Gichana has been reinstated by the Employment and Labour Relations Court. Justice Hellen Wasilwa on Friday suspended his termination by the County Assembly Service Board pending the hearing of the case he filed in the morning.” The prayer for grant of conservatory orders staying termination of the applicants employment vide the Respondents letter dated 6th August 2020 is also allowed,” reads the order. This means that Gichana will preside over the upcoming Nairobi County Speaker elections to replace Beatrice Elachi who resigned. Gichana had asked the court to suspend his removal from office or in the alternative stop the elections because he was the one with the instruments of power to oversee the elections.